The paper discusses the progress and challenges in the field of artificial intelligence, specifically in the area of deep learning and its limitations. It proposes a new notion of integrated information that can potentially resolve the duality between data processing and information processing in AI. This paper is likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it discusses the advancements and limitations in the field of AI. It can also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of neuron networks and deep learning in AI. Additionally, it can be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it discusses the complexity of emulating the human brain in AI systems. Finally, it can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) as it proposes a new notion of integrated information in AI.
